 immersive aspects of this culture, in which Japan’s imperial subjects were mobilized to regularly perform highly orchestrated civil air defense drills throughout the country. The war years in Japan are often portrayed as a landscape of privation and suppression under the censorship of the war machine. But alongside the horrors, pleasure, desire, wonder, creativity, and humor were all still abundantly present in a period before air raids went from being a fearful specter to a deadly reality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAir defensesxSocial aspectszJapan. 0aMilitarizationzJapanxHistoryy20th century. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xSocial aspectszJapan. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aair defense, wartime, gas mask, Japan, visual culture, total war, consumer culture, pleasure, weapons, fashion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107665090 cprintz978022681644940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226816456423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226816456/original  a978-3-11-076650-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-131913-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023